# hello-world

Minimal dispatch baseline — println overhead per call.

```scalascript
def workload(): Unit = println("hello")

val WARMUP = 10
val REPS   = 100
var _w = 0
while _w < WARMUP do
  workload()
  _w += 1

val _t0 = System.currentTimeMillis()
var _r = 0
while _r < REPS do
  workload()
  _r += 1
val _ms = System.currentTimeMillis() - _t0
println(s"BENCH_MS: ${_ms.toDouble / REPS}")
```
